<h3 class="wp-block-heading faq-heading"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong></h3>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1623393125914"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Is push or pull better for shoulders?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Both push and pull exercises are important for shoulders, as they work different muscles. Include both for more balanced and effective push-pull workouts.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1708954782434"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Are shrugs push or pull?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25553964/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Shrugs</a><sup>[14]</sup> are neither push nor pull exercises, but rather elevation and depression exercises. They primarily work the upper trapezius, which helps with raising and lowering the shoulder blades. They also work the levator scapulae, the rhomboids, and the serratus anterior. </p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1708954802650"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Are trapezius muscles push or pull?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">The trapezius muscles are a large and complex muscle group <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK518994/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">with three parts</a>:<sup>[15]</sup> The upper, middle, and lower trapezius. The trapezius neither push nor pull but are involved in upward rotation, adduction, and retraction of the scapula vs. the glenohumeral joint. </p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1708954845157"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>How many shoulder workouts should you perform on push day?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Generally, you can do two to four shoulder exercises on push day. You can do a push-day <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/best-push-day-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">workout</a> once or twice a week, depending on your recovery and schedule.</p> </div> </div>
